			INSTALL
============================================================

Welcome to iLearn.

In order to run iLearn you need the following;

 - MySQL database server
 - Oracle Java Runtime Environment 6 or later

On Ubuntu / Debian based systems you can execute the following command to install MySQL:

   $ sudo apt-get install mysql-server mysql-client
   $ mysql --user=root
     mysql> create database iLearn;
     mysql> use iLearn;
     mysql> grant all on iLearn.* to iLearn@localhost identified by '1l34rn';
     mysql> flush privileges;
     mysql> exit
   
   $ mysql --user=iLearn -p --database=iLearn

To install the Java Runtime Environment you can follow the guide posted by Alin Andrei at the URL below.

   http://www.webupd8.org/2011/09/how-to-install-oracle-java-7-jdk-in.html


